title: Can't Hurt Me
subtitle: Master Your Mind and Defy the Odds
description: New York Times Best Seller Over 4 million copies sold For David Goggins, childhood was a nightmare -- poverty, prejudice, and physical abuse colored his days and haunted his nights. But through self-discipline, mental toughness, and hard work, Goggins transformed himself from a depressed, overweight young man with no future into a U.S. Armed Forces icon and one of the world's top endurance athletes. The only man in history to complete elite training as a Navy SEAL, Army Ranger, and Air Force Tactical Air Controller, he went on to set records in numerous endurance events, inspiring Outside magazine to name him "The Fittest (Real) Man in America." In Can't Hurt Me , he shares his astonishing life story and reveals that most of us tap into only 40% of our capabilities. Goggins calls this The 40% Rule, and his story illuminates a path that anyone can follow to push past pain, demolish fear, and reach their full potential.

description: Disclaimer: The Summary of the original book Can't Hurt Me: Master Your Mind and Defy the Odds By David Goggins.Everyone wants to be fit and healthy, but somehow most people do not find the time to go to the gym or follow up with their exercise sessions. Some famous excuses include spending time with family and friends, working long hours, or even having a 9-5 job can stop people from following up on their dreams.Most people postpone their dreams for another day. They forget about their commitments to stay fit and healthy or to achieve something in the present. What is the difference between David Goggins and these people? Hard work and determination.David Goggins narrated his experiences from early childhood when his abusive father did not beat him, his mother, and his brother when they did not obey, but he also forced them to work hard until midnight. His childhood was marked by many abusive experiences; he used to fall asleep during courses and finally developed toxic stress.Among other symptoms, David could not learn as easily as others, due to his condition. By his late teenage years, he was barely able to read. Without a bright opportunity for his future and challenged by poverty, past traumas, and continuous stress, David decided that he wished to join the army.However, the path was not smooth, as he walked out on his dream because the fear of swimming conquered him. Finding his refuge in food, he gains weight and has a dead-end job as a pest exterminator. Soon, he finds a new motivation as he sees a documentary about Navy SEALs. This is the crucial point in which he turns around his life, starts a strict fitness routine, and makes his dreams come true.

description: This audiobook is a comprehensive summary of Can't Hurt Me . David Goggins had a mission: The only way he could make it into the Navy SEALs training camp was to lose more than 100 pounds in less than three months. After years of neglecting his body, he went for a jog and keeled over in pain a half-mile later. Fast-forward a year, and he’s engaging the enemy as a full-fledged US Navy SEAL. How the heck did that happen? Today, David Goggins is an ultramarathoner, retired US Navy SEAL, former Guinness World Record holder, and all-around unstoppable warrior. Can’t Hurt Me has brought countless people through Goggins’ hell and back - from an abusive childhood and impoverished adolescence to the pinnacles of human achievement. Goggins takes the listener under his wing not only to recount a fascinating journey but to explain the methods that he used to overcome everything that life threw against him. So many of us live our lives within the limits that we staked out long ago. We run less than our farthest distance. We study and learn less than we did when we were in school. We work less than we did on our first day. Can’t Hurt Me explains the benefits of flipping this script and living in a constant state of engaging with the impossible. That process of breaking through the walls of life is what this book is about. And every second of it is a brutal, bloody, beautiful ride that you don’t want to miss. Simply, this book is for anyone who dares to engage with the impossible. Disclaimer: This is a summary of David Goggins' Can't Hurt Me . Download and start reading immediately! David Goggins is a retired Navy SEAL, renowned ultra-athlete, and former world record-holder for most pull-ups in 24 hours. He was featured in Jesse Itzler’s book Living With A SEAL after Itzler invited him to spend a month in his home, where Goggins trained and challenged him to reach heights he hadn’t before thought were possible. Goggins has traveled the country many times over sharing inspiration with countless listeners. Today, he speaks to corporations, universities, and professional athletic teams around the world and sits on interviews with various media personalities. But for many years, his primary audience was young students in middle school and high school. He is the only person in the history of the U.S. Armed Forces to have completed Air Force Tactical Air Controller training, U.S. Army Ranger training, and SEAL training. To date, he has competed in 60+ triathlons, ultramarathons, and ultra triathlons, where he regularly sets new course records and places among the top finishers. Abused. Outcast. Derided. Unremarkable. Stuttering. A waste. These words characterize David Goggins’ start in life. He shouldn’t have been anything — that was clear from the start. But every time some obstacle showed up to beat him down, he had one response: You can’t hurt me . Defying all odds, he rose up and made something of himself. He became an icon in the armed forces. He inspired countless numbers of students. He set new bars of excellence in every domain he set foot in. Through it all, not everything went his way. He faced numerous failures, injustices, and just plain bad breaks over the years. There were times when he quit and became lost. There were times when he drove himself or others too hard... and paid for it later. He doesn’t pretend to have gotten everything right along the way, but he does share his entire story along with the lessons he learned at each stage. Can’t Hurt Me is Goggins’ guide for anyone who wants to live beyond the easy standards embraced by most of modern society. For anyone who wants to leave behind their life of numbness and empty distractions. By applying the lessons contained in this book to your own life, you too can live an extraordinary life. Goggins proves time and again that you don’t need to be born with superior genetics or a special upbringing to still live a powerful, meaningful life that you’re proud of and grateful for when you reach the end of your days.
